+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Uce72eHrUWCVzZCDdCx9qE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me think about the approach for `findSwappedWires` before coding. The key insight is that a ripple-carry adder has a very specific structure per bit position. For each bit `i` (except bit 0):\n\n- **XOR gate**: `x[i] XOR y[i] -> t[i]` (partial sum)\n- **XOR gate**: `t[i] XOR c[i-1] -> z[i]` (final sum)  \n- **AND gate**: `x[i] AND y[i] -> a[i]` (generate carry)\n- **AND gate**: `t[i] AND c[i-1] -> b[i]` (propagate carry)\n- **OR gate**: `a[i] OR b[i] -> c[i]` (carry out)\n\nFor bit 0:\n- **XOR gate**: `x00 XOR y00 -> z00`\n- **AND gate**: `x00 AND y00 -> c00`\n\nThe approach: analyze the circuit structure and validate each gate against the expected adder pattern. When a gate's output doesn't match the expected pattern, identify the swaps."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":219,"cache_read_input_tokens":20826,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":219},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55d498c5-dcec-4c3d-b8c9-b8f0671dc5a6","uuid":"dd15c434-9d2d-4c4e-8beb-3b3d2d22dba2"}
